spirit:component.spirit:name: CPM_bd_axis_ila_0_0
spirit:component.spirit:description: The Integrated Logic Analyzer (ILA with AXIS Interface) core is a customizable logic analyzer core that can be used to monitor any internal signal of your design. The ILA core includes many advanced features of modern logic analyzers, including Boolean trigger equations, customizable data capture buffer depth, and optional trigger input/output ports. Because the ILA core is synchronous to the design being monitored, all design clock constraints that are applied to your design are also applied to the components inside the ILA core. Run-time interaction with this core requires the use of the Vivado logic analyzer feature.
